Here are three highly acclaimed science fiction movies, each with an IMDb rating above 8.0 or a Rotten Tomatoes Tomatometer score above 70%.

**1. "Inception"**

- **Director:** Christopher Nolan
- **Release Date:** July 16, 2010
- **Plot Summary:** "Inception" follows Dom Cobb, a thief who specializes in infiltrating people's dreams to steal secrets. He's offered a chance to have his criminal record erased by performing an almost impossible task: planting an idea into someone's subconscious, known as "inception."
- **IMDb Rating:** 8.8/10
- **Positive Review:** [Roger Ebert's Review](https://www.rogerebert.com/reviews/inception-2010)
- **Negative Review:** [Slant Magazine's Review](https://www.slantmagazine.com/film/inception/)

**2. "The Matrix"**

- **Directors:** Lana Wachowski, Lilly Wachowski
- **Release Date:** March 31, 1999
- **Plot Summary:** "The Matrix" centers on Neo, a hacker who discovers that reality as he knows it is a simulation controlled by intelligent machines. He joins a group of rebels to fight against the machines and uncover the truth.
- **IMDb Rating:** 8.7/10
- **Positive Review:** [Empire's Review](https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/matrix-review/)
- **Negative Review:** [The Washington Post's Review](https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/style/longterm/movies/videos/matrixhunter.htm)

**3. "Blade Runner 2049"**

- **Director:** Denis Villeneuve
- **Release Date:** October 6, 2017
- **Plot Summary:** Set 30 years after the original "Blade Runner," Officer K, a new blade runner, unearths a long-hidden secret that could plunge society into chaos. His discovery leads him on a quest to find Rick Deckard, a former blade runner who has been missing for decades.
- **Rotten Tomatoes Tomatometer:** 88%
- **Positive Review:** [The Guardian's Review](https://www.theguardian.com/film/2017/oct/05/blade-runner-2049-review-harrison-ford-ryan-gosling)
- **Negative Review:** [The New Yorker's Review](https://www.newyorker.com/culture/richard-brody/blade-runner-2049-reviewed)

These films are celebrated for their innovative storytelling and significant impact on the science fiction genre.

